In another annotated game, I said that I was tempted to take dxe4, and an annotator remarked that that capture is often calling to black but that taking with the f-pawn will almost always work out better. In this case, I like that the pawn can be supported by the queenside chain instead of having to play g6 to guard it with a pawn. I also like giving my bishop some extra room and maybe opportunities for the rook.

IMPLODe   K analysis:
Initiative - no one seems to have an advantage
Material - even
Pawn structure - I'm ahead. He has three pawn islands and doubled pawns
Lines & squares - I feel he's ahead because of his rook on f1 (temporarily) and his queen controlling the g-file is stronger than mine controlling e7-h4.
Officers - I'm ahead; my bishops are in better position (though only until he plays a3).
Development - even
King safety - even

Looks to me like we're running out of pieces, and I'm not feeling excited about breaking through in the pawn endgame.
